author: Carrie Anderson
title: Memphis moves up in AP Poll
text:
Memphis moves up in AP Poll Posted: 
379 days since their last loss. And now, the Memphis Tigers are number 16 in the Associated Press college football poll. Memphis moving up two spots, thanks to their latest victory, a 66-42 win over Tulsa Friday night. The Tigers racking up over 700 yards of total offense against the Golden Hurricane, and Paxton Lynch recording his 6th straight game of over 300 yards passing, throwing for 447 yards and 4 touchdowns. Memphis also moves up a spot in the Amway Coaches poll. They now sit at number 16 in that poll as well.
